Four suspected ISIS members yesterday were remanded for three days to allow police to complete investigations.Ali Musa, Mwinyi Musa, Khamisi Hakim and Yasin Ahmed appeared before chief magistrate Julius Nang ea.They were arrested last Friday. Police said the suspects planned to commit acts of terrorism at unspecified locations in Mombasa and Kwale counties. In a sworn affidavit, an officer said mobile phones were recovered from their residence and are being analysed. The prosecution told the court their accomplices are still at large and asked for the suspects to be detained for 14 days. Nang ea granted police three days. The case will be mentioned on Friday.